#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:5
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:7
msgid ""
"A *Spot* lamp emits a cone-shaped beam of light from the tip of the cone, in "
"a given direction."
msgstr ""
"Une lampe *Spot* émet un faisceau de lumière en forme de cône depuis la "
"pointe du cône, dans une direction donnée."

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:10
msgid ""
"The *Spot* light is the most complex of the light objects and indeed, for a "
"long time, among the most used thanks to the fact that it was the only one "
"able to cast shadows. Nowadays, with a ray tracer integrated into Blender's "
"internal render engine, all lamps can cast shadows (except *Hemi*). Even so, "
"*Spot* lamps' shadow buffers are much faster to render than ray-traced "
"shadows, especially when blurred/softened, and spot lamps also provide other "
"functionality such as \"volumetric\" halos."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:21
msgid "Lamp options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:26
msgid "Common Lamp options of a Spot."
msgstr "Options de lampe communes d'un Spot."

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:30
msgid "Distance, Energy and Color"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:30
msgid ""
"These settings are common to most types of lamps, and are described in :doc:"
"`Light Properties </render/blender_render/lighting/lights/lamp_panel>`."
msgstr ""
"Ces réglages sont communs à la plupart des types de lampes, et sont décrits "
"dans :doc:`Propriétés des lumières </render/blender_render/lighting/lights/"
"lamp_panel>`."

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:33
msgid "This Layer Only, Negative, Diffuse and Specular"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:33
msgid ""
"These settings control what the lamp affects, as described in :ref:`What "
"Light Affects <bi-lamp-influence>`."
msgstr ""
"Ces réglages contrôlent ce que la lampe affecte, comme décrit dans :ref:`Ce "
"que la lumière affecte <bi-lamp-influence>`."

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:43
msgid "Light Falloff and Sphere"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:36
msgid ""
"These settings control how the light of the *Spot* decays with distance. "
"See :doc:`Light Attenuation </render/blender_render/lighting/lights/"
"light_attenuation>` for details."
msgstr ""
"Ces réglages contrôlent la manière dont la lumière du *Spot* décline avec la "
"distance. Voir :doc:`Atténuation de la lumière </render/blender_render/"
"lighting/lights/light_attenuation>` pour les détails."

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:42
msgid ""
"Changing the Spot options also changes the appearance of the spotlight as "
"displayed in the 3D View."
msgstr ""
"Changer les options de *Spot* change aussi l'apparence du spot tel "
"qu'affiché dans la Vue 3D."

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:46
msgid "Shadows"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:51
msgid "Shadow panel set to Ray Shadow."
msgstr "Panneau Shadow avec Ray Shadow activé."

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:54
msgid ""
"Spotlights can use either ray-traced shadows or buffered shadows. Either of "
"the two can provide various extra options. Ray-traced shadows are generally "
"more accurate, with extra capabilities such as transparent shadows, although "
"they are quite slower to render."
msgstr ""
"Les lumières spot peuvent utiliser les ombres en lancer de rayon ou bien les "
"ombres en cache. Les uns comme les autres peuvent fournir diverses options "
"supplémentaires. Les ombres en lancer de rayon sont généralement plus "
"précis, avec des possibilités supplémentaires telles que les ombres "
"transparentes, bien qu'ils nécessitent bien plus de temps pour le rendu. "

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:60
msgid "No Shadow"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:60
msgid ""
"Choose this to turn shadows off for this spot lamp. This can be useful to "
"add some discreet directed light to a scene."
msgstr ""
"Choisissez cette option pour désactiver les ombres pour cette lampe *Spot*. "
"Cela peut être utile d'ajouter un peu de lumière dirigée discrète à une "
"scène."

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:69
msgid "Buffer Shadow"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:63
msgid ""
"*Buffered Shadows* are also known as depth map shadows. Shadows are created "
"by calculating differences in the distance from the light to scene objects. "
"See :doc:`Buffered Shadows </render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/"
"buffered_shadows>` for full details on using this feature. Buffered shadows "
"are more complex to set up and involve more faking, but the speed of "
"rendering is a definite advantage. Nevertheless, it shares with other lamp "
"types common shadow options described in :doc:`/render/blender_render/"
"lighting/shadows/shadow_panel`."
msgstr ""
"*Buffered Shadows* sont aussi connues comme *depth map shadows*. Les ombres "
"sont créées en calculant les différences dans la distance de la lumière aux "
"objets de la scène. Voir :doc:`Buffered Shadows </render/blender_render/"
"lighting/lamps/spot/buffered_shadows>` pour des détails complets sur "
"l'utilisation de cette fonction. Les *Buffered shadows* sont plus complexes "
"à installer et impliquent plus d'artefacts, mais la vitesse de rendu est un "
"avantage certain. Toutefois la lampe *Spot* partage avec d'autres types de "
"lampes des options d'ombre communes décrites dans :doc:`/render/"
"blender_render/lighting/shadows/shadow_panel`."

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:74
msgid "Ray Shadow"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:72
msgid ""
"The ray-traced shadows settings of this lamp are shared with other lamps, "
"and are described in :doc:`Raytraced Properties </render/blender_render/"
"lighting/shadows/raytraced_properties>`."
msgstr ""
"Les réglages d'ombre en lancer de rayon de cette lampe sont partagés avec "
"d'autres lampes, et sont décrits dans :doc:`Propriétés en lancer de rayon </"
"render/blender_render/lighting/shadows/raytraced_properties>`."

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:77
msgid "Spot Shape"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:93
msgid "Size"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:80
msgid ""
"The size of the outer cone of a *Spot*, which largely controls the circular "
"area a *Spot* light covers. This slider in fact controls the angle at the "
"top of the lighting cone, and can be between (1.0 to 180.0)."
msgstr ""
"La taille du cône extérieur d'un *Spot*, qui contrôle largement la zone "
"circulaire couverte par la lumière d'un *Spot*. Ce curseur contrôle en fait "
"l'angle au sommet du cône de lumière, et dont la valeur peut être entre (1.0 "
"à 180.0)."

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:85
msgid "Changing the spot *Size* option."
msgstr "Modifier l'option *Size* du spot."

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:124
msgid "Blend"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:96
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The *Blend* slider controls the inner cone of the *Spot*. The *Blend* value "
"can be between (0.0 to 1.0). The value is proportional and represents that "
"amount of space that the inner cone should occupy inside the outer cone "
"*Size*."
msgstr ""
"Le curseur *Blend* contrôle le cône interne du *Spot*. La valeur *Blend* "
"peut être entre (0.0 à 1.0). La valeur est proportionnel et représente la "
"quantité d'espace que le cône interne devrait occuper dans la taille "
"(*Size*) du cône externe."

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:101
msgid ""
"The inner cone boundary line indicates the point at which light from the "
"*Spot* will start to blur/soften; before this point its light will mostly be "
"full strength. The larger the value of *Blend* the more blurred/soft the "
"edges of the spotlight will be, and the smaller the inner cone's circular "
"area will be (as it starts to blur/soften earlier)."
msgstr ""
"La ligne délimitant le cône interne indique le point auquel la lumière du "
"*Spot* va commencer à devenir floue/douce ; avant ce point sa lumière sera "
"principalement à la pleine puissance. Plus la valeur de *Blend* est grande, "
"plus les bords de la lumière du spot seront flous/doux, et plus la zone "
"circulaire du cône interne sera petite (comme elle commence à devenir floue/"
"douce plus tôt). "

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:106
msgid ""
"To make the *Spot* have a sharper falloff rate and therefore less blurred/"
"soft edges, decrease the value of *Blend*. Setting *Blend* to 0.0 results in "
"very sharp spotlight edges, without any transition between light and shadow."
msgstr ""
"Pour faire que le *Spot* ait un vignettage plus et ainsi des bords moins "
"flous/doux, diminuez la valeur de *Blend*. Mettre *Blend* à 0.0 conduit à "
"des bords de lumière de spot très tranchants, sans aucune transition entre "
"lumière et ombre. "

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:110
msgid ""
"The falloff rate of the *Spot* lamp light is a ratio between the *Blend* and "
"*Size* values; the larger the circular gap between the two, the more gradual "
"the light fades between *Blend* and *Size*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:113
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"*Blend* and *Size* only control the *Spot* light cone's aperture and "
"softness (\"radial\" falloff); they do not control the shadow's softness as "
"shown below."
msgstr ""
"*Blend* et *Size* contrôlent seulement l'ouverture et la douceur "
"(atténuation \"radiale*) du cône de lumière *Spot* ; ils ne contrôlent pas "
"la douceur de l'ombre comme affiché ci dessous."

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:119
msgid ""
"Render showing the soft edge spotlighted area and the sharp/hard object "
"shadow."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:122
msgid ""
"Notice in the picture above that the object's shadow is sharp as a result of "
"the ray tracing, whereas the spotlight edges are soft. If you want other "
"items to cast soft shadows within the *Spot* area, you will need to alter "
"other shadow settings."
msgstr ""
"Notez dans l'image ci-dessus que l'ombre de l'objet est tranchante en tant "
"que résultat du lancer de rayons, alors que les bords de la lumière spot "
"sont doux. Si vous voulez d'autres éléments pour jeter des ombres douces à "
"l'intérieur de la zone du *Spot*, vous aurez besoin de modifier d'autres "
"réglages d'ombre."

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:126
msgid "Square"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:127
msgid ""
"The *Square* button makes a *Spot* light cast a square light area, rather "
"than the default circular one."
msgstr ""
"Le bouton *Square* fait qu'une lumière *Spot* projette une zone de lumière "
"carrée, plutôt qu'une de forme circulaire par défaut."

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:128
msgid "Show Cone"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/lighting/lamps/spot/introduction.rst:129
msgid ""
"Draw a transparent cone in 3D View to visualize which objects are contained "
"in it."
msgstr ""
"Dessine un cône transparent dans la Vue 3D pour visualiser quels objets sont "
"contenus dedans."

